text: Lycée Français René Cassin d'Oslo () is a French international school in Oslo, Norway."Locaux" (Archive). Lycée Français René Cassin d'Oslo. Retrieved on 23 March 2015. "Skovveien 9, 0257 Oslo" The school serves the levels preschool through the final year of lycée, terminale (high school)."Structure Pédagogique." Lycée Français René Cassin d'Oslo. Retrieved on 23 March 2015. The school originated from the Vestheim School (Vestheim skole), founded by five people in 1891: Frederik Fredriksen, Nils Grøterud, Wilhelm Myhre, Hans H. K. Hougen, and Ole Jacobe Skattum. In 2017 the Norwegian state gave NOK 4 million to the school because it needed funding to pay for new teachers and school supplies."
